Here‚Äôs a sample Risk Assessment and Risk Control for your Meeting Attendance Tapping System ‚Äî written in a simple and clear format suitable for documentation or presentation:


---

Risk Assessment and Risk Control

Risk ID	Risk Description	Impact	Likelihood	Risk Level	Risk Control / Mitigation

R1	Unauthorized access to the system	High	Medium	High	Implement user authentication and role-based access control. Use strong passwords and restrict admin functions.
R2	Duplicate attendance entries	Medium	Medium	Medium	Enable duplicate detection and validation before saving attendance records.
R3	System downtime during meeting hours	High	Low	Medium	Regularly back up the database and perform scheduled maintenance during off-hours.
R4	Data loss or corruption	High	Low	Medium	Use automated database backups and implement recovery procedures.
R5	Incorrect user tapping (e.g., tapping wrong ID)	Low	Medium	Low	Display user confirmation details (e.g., name, department) after tapping to verify correctness.
R6	Unauthorized modification of attendance records	High	Low	Medium	Restrict editing privileges to authorized personnel only and maintain audit logs.
R7	Browser or network connectivity issues	Medium	Medium	Medium	Implement offline logging or retry mechanisms and notify users of connection issues.
R8	Privacy concerns regarding employee data	High	Low	Medium	Store personal data securely, comply with data protection policies, and limit data access.



