üßæ Sample 1 ‚Äî Table Format (Simplified)

Risk	Description	Risk Level	Control / Mitigation

Data Security	Unauthorized users may access the system and view attendance records.	High	Apply user authentication, role-based access, and password protection.
Duplicate Records	Employees may tap multiple times, causing duplicate entries.	Medium	Enable duplicate detection logic before saving.
Data Loss	Data may be lost due to server or power failure.	High	Schedule automatic backups and use stable database hosting.
Incorrect Entry	Wrong ID tapped by employee.	Low	Display user details for confirmation after tapping.
System Unavailability	The system may go down during important meetings.	Medium	Perform preventive maintenance and monitoring.
Privacy Violation	Employee information may be exposed.	High	Encrypt sensitive data and limit access to authorized users only.



---

üõ°Ô∏è Sample 2 ‚Äî Paragraph / Summary Style

Risk Assessment:
The system may face several operational and security risks such as unauthorized access, data loss, and duplicate attendance entries. There is also a possibility of downtime during meetings, which could affect real-time monitoring.

Risk Control:
To address these, the system implements user validation, role-based access control, and duplicate entry prevention. Regular backups are conducted to secure data integrity. Audit logs track all modifications, while database access is restricted to authorized personnel only. Preventive maintenance schedules are also in place to ensure system reliability.


---

üß© Sample 3 ‚Äî Detailed Style (for formal documentation)

Category	Identified Risk	Impact	Preventive Control	Corrective Action

Access Control	Unauthorized access by non-registered users	High	Implement login validation, assign user roles	Lock account after failed login attempts and review access logs
Data Integrity	Duplicate or inaccurate attendance entries	Medium	Apply duplicate check and validation rules	Allow admin correction with approval record
System Reliability	Application crashes or server downtime	High	Conduct system health checks and backups	Restore from backup and notify admin immediately
Data Privacy	Leakage of employee data	High	Encrypt stored data and apply secure connections (HTTPS)	Report incident and reset credentials
Operational Error	Incorrect tapping by employees	Low	Display confirmation screen after tap	Allow re-validation by meeting in-charge



